repo.description: The most widely used Python to C compiler
repo.name: cython

body:
With #3440, I had the module hashes for `cython.inline` code strings generated once in the fast path and again in the regular path. This would probably cause them to be calculated twice if the code string had been seen before but not with the same language version and arguments' signature.

https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/34714637936756abb42a5732b08167b767945087/Cython/Build/Inline.py#L169-L173

https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/34714637936756abb42a5732b08167b767945087/Cython/Build/Inline.py#L198-L199

commit.message: Add test to ensure Shadow.inline() recompiles code with different language versions.
Take language version into account when taking cached fast path in Build.cython_inline().
New line at end of file.

Goals:
– New version scheme: 3.x instead of 0.x.
– Change default `language_level` from `2` to `3`.
– Change default for `binding` directive from `False` to `True`.
– Fix some Python compatibility issues (if possible, allowing for breaking changes).
